<dl id="n37005r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37005r">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37005r"> 5(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> baptism of the dead / &mdash; by proxy <small>Black</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n37005r"><li>FW 537.08 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/lexrB.htm#n37005r">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rB/l39rB.htm#n37005r">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n37005r">MS BL 47484b-471v</ms> </li><li>JJA 59:226 <a name="rBd15" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rBd15">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rB/rBd15.htm#n37005r">Draft: III&sect;3B.15</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Mormons]</font> believe in and practise <mark>baptism for the dead</mark>. They baptise for their remote ancestors, and the more ancestors they can find the more they can baptise for <mark>by proxy</mark>, and the richer they will eventually be in relatives in heaven. <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWB"><cite title="source">Brigham Young</cite></a> (1925) 325</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
